t="1"><mxGeometry x="1652" y="1434" width="200" height="108" as="geometry"/></mxCell></object><object label="Meat-eater problem&lt;br&gt;(saved humans eat animals)&lt;br&gt;[1+2+5+7]&lt;br&gt;→ Shrimp Welfare Project&lt;br&gt;(Michael Dickens, Vasco Grilo)" tooltip="&lt;b&gt;parochial + far_away_humans + animals_somewhat + animals_matter_a_lot + meat_eater_problem&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;The meat-eater problem: a dollar of human global health also buys decades of that person&#x27;s meat consumption, and factory farming it causes suffering the animal circle now counts. Each present-human org is charged an additive penalty — farmed-animal life-years caused per human DALY, times the suffering per factory-farmed life-year, times the animal&#x27;s welfare range. Under a heavy animal welfare range the penalty can exceed the human benefit, so saving human lives looks net-harmful. Only bites once animals count, so it requires animals_somewhat; and it is a near-term human-vs-animal get-off point, not combined with astronomical-stakes longtermism (no_discounting_future_humans), where x-risk dominates and the meat bookkeeping is moot. || Chain: 0 parochial → 1 far_away_humans → 2 animals_somewhat → 5 animals_matter_a_lot → 7 meat_eater_problem" link="https://www.squiggle-language.com/playground#code=eJylVn9v2kgQ%2FSqj6E4HXEJskx8NJ%2F4ghLZR6bUiuatOpaKLPcZ7We9au%2Bs4NM13v1kbAgRzV%2BmQEMYz%2B2bmzezbfTyIMGa5sAMV4UH34PgYer0e3GrGJVgFoWbfFvRQSJjkgeefQKG0iO45FlD402B6Oj2HhrEqg%%2FwUau%2FCbda%2FWb4%2B3Dcvx1ewWwBc5Soich2tlg1HiNut2hqkfEQJDWgTMYxSUgl1hXXhAsYx%2B6HaEbXAqXnxFFGKTC9gBmFiHnI6fkQLoevP4yHxIFmokQokM8TS%2FQRI0K5UUz416pzQs2l0jQGcOH9DINraChN9R6p%2BChlc8ltHiFcfrgdDpqUj1F59o7bMEF5xcTiI%2Bo%2FTAQ9eJxIgAxVJvAtigyjZ4vX9k5dQK996nwKFGKGlMkbaqGDqFw8v%2FLxfOcUqlzSQMQstDkTl0ze%2FVl2yrl29kRq1UC3oOHD0T645kQ%2BTeQ82irE5eKdLJPxgolkabzj0FlW5AWULuPpjsOqmoBqtonYsvvtwFlPzonNIts2BZ7nbOcnlMREFlxEs3xutn3OKp9XQenDhIgxqulFf655SFKU0wwMmGXGapUlSF4DlPR2RXxnmWrZHcHv0dyw%2B5LVKyUE09fxxupqTZl%2F4PyjKu6Ix87U8crIA37PBf%2FG3FwPZeQaQrByB2Y1F2XLafff3SS0jcaYqs34rmQ88sua6cG7cN5xThWgq9r07Y1ldw7S99af0tt78flBXlr%2FTUNrq%2FJffwz1R4hp%2FQsRrZqyyxEmDSyUqhmChzGBjTHKw11CO0tC%2FeD%2FEVofY2%2Bu1RHyubjqj%2F4CYlg7Hc5IX3%2F60t3UtWhL8yxPl2fDWtNCRUZSPOL3hX7TcvbizIQst8ZJJ3f6bELlzo0efHYVPAJtcuzC5GCkQtJBp3FwV4nc5OAQiuiZ2K47FGWjVgWbVLRPs9A4KjWkc37R8c%2Ba8HS4HcO1vBJ0sahH31SkF6BnZxcnXlAPSseQAHd1oII1twto9N%2B%2FbtaH2BK17RhnZ17wyt8N0b9%2BD8cwWGIPpdWY0QmMuTYJz%2FaE2ZTG7TCnndNXJ7tRbqnFb939BWGEbJ5jPfCWpjpgOhc6wQ5a%2FQG9p6ebWlxBeh1%2FB%2FITaTLdcAzhGGgkVaoZXRVoEiM0e%2FjeVfJlhN0A%2FdHo9fBqD58vxL4EqekUGBajm4BxpQwwprsL02GyJ70dAVkDf3FbVtOR6e5ePRhxY9saad8abJR%2FjNL2ctGottQhPH5%2F%2BA4P7Y0YT006aGfuMtWDJdBn78tSCW5rr2O3b69v1tu5C%2BWtlRPhs9WdjISCUxaGNvPGDY8iOI%2FN6BN58PQPCl7kbQ%3D%3D" id="w1_2_5_7"><mxCell style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fontSize=11;fillColor=#eec2a8;strokeColor=#c65a2e;fontColor=#5a2a10;" vertex="1" parent="1"><mxGeometry x="347" y="956" width="244" height="108" as="geometry"/></mxCell></object><object label="Net-negative lives&lt;br&gt;(animal suffering dominates)&lt;br&gt;[1+2+5+7+8]&lt;br&gt;→ Shrimp Welfare Project&lt;br&gt;(Brian Tomasik, David Benatar)" tooltip="&lt;b&gt;parochial + far_away_humans + animals_somewhat + animals_matter_a_lot + meat_eater_problem + net_negative_animal_lives&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;The net-negative-lives hypothesis: factory-farmed and wild animals endure more suffering than wellbeing, so their lives are not worth living. Reducing that suffering is worth more per dollar (you are mitigating a catastrophe, not improving a good life), most of all for the astronomical wild-invertebrate populations. Combined with the meat-eater problem it drives human charities firmly net-negative — every human sustained means more net-negative farmed lives. Presupposes counting wild/invertebrate animals, so it requires animals_matter_a_lot; and like the meat-eater problem it is a near-term animal get-off point, not combined with astronomical-stakes longtermism (no_discounting_future_humans). || Chain: 0 parochial → 1 far_away_humans → 2 animals_somewhat → 5 animals_matter_a_lot → 7 meat_eater_problem → 8 net_negative_animal_lives" link="https://www.squiggle-language.com/playground#code=eJylVmFv4kYQ%2FSujqFWBJsQ2BBIqPhBC7qLjeieS9lQdJ26xx3ib9a61uw7hcvnvnbUhQID2pCIhjGf2zcyb2bf7dBRhzHJh%2ByrCo87R6Sl0u12404xLsApCzb4t6GEuYZwHnt%2BEudIieuA4h7k%2FCSZnk%2FbkHCrGqgzOq27xWBJIz5g8zSxXEsKEsDrgQca0ChPOhIPyLwLwIWZ6wuZsMUnylEmzMgTAJE%2BZMBOjUpwnzK4sZy%2BWlFmLtHoi1Iu1DSkyO6EvWTKtpgLTle0cJNqJxBmz%2FAEnJcxE0LMpMh6wMAG2TpsbYPBxYRN6jrlAIELWZnMK1qXFosgcg0ZikUs0oHQBpvGEqmUpUiLc0HubYEnELwbiXIYFxm8QqjRThsvZ2oHWyggJkV7xMjVjmYyYUBIhpTaJOnx96cLg4atL1S3HxwxDSwsfmMgRVFwgrBtWL8Au0ViY5gvIXRi30OBmYR24TTRPM%2FiEgtqD8FGrvwm3XP1m8Ptg1LsbXMF0ATOUqInrerZYTQdG3G7RVCPjMUjqUZGMY5KQCqwrrgkXMI7dD9GMrgVKz4ijjFJgegFTChHzkNPzMVwOrj%2BMBsSBZqJAmCOfJZboI0aEcvOa8K9l54SaSaWpxXDh%2FQz9G6goTfWeqPgkZTPJbR4hXH64G%2FSrlI9RefaO2zBBecXE4iPqP0wEXXgaS4AMVSbwLYoMoxeLV%2FfOXECvfuZ85ijEFCmTN9RCB1G6eH7p4%2FnOKVS5pIGIWWhzJi6ZvP%2Bz6JRzbRyIVNsDXYOKDyeH4Kpj%2BTyWs2irEJeL11wm4wVjydJ4x6GxrMgLKF3G0x2HVTUB1WwTsWX364GzNtvE5jzbNgWe52ztJiUxlnMuomk%2BM9s%2BrdLnPCh8mBAxRnt60ZtpHpJe5TQDfWaZsVplCZJXHyW9XRHfWKZadKfY5bfsoWD1SgnB9E28sbpcU%2BQfOP%2BojDvksTM1vCJynz9wwb8xN9cDGbmGEKzcgVnNRdFy2v33twltoxGmajO%2BKxlP%2FKJmevAunHecUwXoqjY9e2vZvYP0vfWn8PZefX6Ql9p%2F01DbqvzXH0P9EWJq%2F0JEbU%2FZxQiTBs6V2jMEjyMCG2GUh7uENpaE%2BsH%2FI3R%2FjIO5lkfI5%2FlVb%2FgXEMPa6XBG%2BvrTl86mrkVbmmd5ujwb1poWKjKS4hG%2Fr%2FSblrNXxypkuTVOOrnTZxMqd2504bOr4Alok2MHxkdDFZIOOo2D%2B1LkxkfHMI9eiO24c1NW9qpglYr2aRYqJ4UCnPntoF2F5%2BPtEK7jpZ6LxX7wTUHaxgxa7XbL349Jh5AAd7egcjW3C6j03l9X90fYkrStEEGr6fvBboTezXs4hf4SeiCtxoyOX8y1SXh2IMqmLm5H8ZuNRms3yh3196273yAMkc1y3A%2B8JagO2Ku3Ws0dtP2n84GGbgpxCeldNHYgP5Eg0%2FXGEI6BSlKmmtE9gcYwQnOA7l0ZX0Y42%2BV5OLweXB3g85XSFyB7OgWGxegGYFTKAozo4sJ0mBxIb0c91sBf3H7VdF66i1cXhtzYukbatAYrxR%2BjtL1cVMr9dAxP3x%2B%2Fw2N9I8ZzlU7ZqbtJdWEJ9Nn7spSBu713sbu3N7frvdyB4lbLifDp6kJGKsEpC0M7eeN6RxGcx2b0sTx6%2FgemYPD7" id="w1_2_5_7_8"><mxCell s